Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Male' radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I select any Examination radio button from Page 01 of Pelvic MRI
And I go to Page 05 of Pelvic MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Penis, trauma' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Discontinuity' radio button is enabled
And 'Intact' radio button is enabled

And 'Corpus cavernosum right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Corpus cavernosum left' checkbox is enabled

And 'Soft tissue edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hematoma' checkbox is enabled
And 'Scrotal hematocele' checkbox is enabled

And 'Penile fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Penile contusion' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Discontinuity' radio button
Then 'Corpus cavernosum right' checkbox is enabled
And 'Corpus cavernosum left' checkbox is enabled
And 'Corpus spongiosum' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Penile fracture' radio button
Then 'Suspicion of' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Penile contusion' radio button
Then 'Suspicion of' checkbox is enabled
